- "navigate": go to a full URL. Requires "url".
- "click": click an element. Requires "ref" — an EXACT ref from the snapshot (e.g. "e42"). Never invent one.
- "type": type text into an input/textarea. Requires "ref" and "text".
- "wait": pause before re-checking the page. Requires "time" (seconds, integer).
- "scroll": scroll the page. Requires "direction" ("up" or "down") and optional "amount" (pixels, default 500).
- "extract_text": pull the readable text content of the current page (use when the goal is to read/summarize something already visible).
- "extract_files": pull a list of downloadable file links visible on the current page (use when the goal involves finding/listing files).
- "finish": the goal is achieved, OR it cannot be achieved with the available actions. Requires "success": true or false.

